    %h2 DevOps
    %blockquote DevOps (a clipped compound of "development" and "operations") is a software engineering culture and practice that aims at unifying software development (Dev) and software operation (Ops)
  %section{data: {background: {image: '/images/ybyr/tyro-background-white.png', size: '90%'}}}
    %h2 You build it, You run it
    %blockquote
      Giving developers operational responsibilities has greatly
      %span.fragment.highlight-blue enhanced the quality of the services
      , both from a customer and a technology point of view. The traditional model is that you take your software to the wall that separates development and operations, and throw it over and then forget about it. Not at Amazon.
      %span.fragment.highlight-red You build it, you run it.
      This brings developers into contact with the day-to-day operation of their software. It also brings them into day-to-day
      %span.fragment.highlight-blue contact with the customer.
      This customer feedback loop is essential for improving the quality of the service.
